#users Collection

Purpose: Core user identity, authentication linkage, role, sector/profession designation, and overall account status. This is the central document for any logged-in user.
Document ID: userId (Should match Firebase Authentication UID)
Key Fields:
email: String (Verified)
role: String ('employer' or 'professional') - Determined at signup.
primarySector: String ('pharmacy', 'medical', ...) - Determined at signup.
primaryProfession: String (e.g., 'pharmacist', 'pharmacy_assistant', ...) - Applicable if role='professional', determined at signup.
profileStatus: String ('incomplete', 'complete', 'pending_verification', 'verified') - Tracks profile setup stage.
profileId: String (Reference ID to the specific document in employerProfiles OR professionalProfiles) - Crucial link established during profile creation.
createdAt: Timestamp
lastLoginAt: Timestamp
isActive: Boolean (Allows disabling account access)
notificationPreferences: Map (User settings for communication)
consents: Map (Tracking agreement to ToS, Privacy Policy versions, etc. e.g., { tosVersion: '1.1', privacyVersion: '1.0', acceptedAt: Timestamp })

