###Collection: facilityProfiles

Document ID: profileId (Unique ID, referenced in the users document)
userId: String (Back-reference to the users document) - Top Level
1. identityLegal (Map) - Core Legal & Business Identification
* Purpose: Essential, verifiable legal identity of the employing entity. High importance for contracts and compliance.
* Fields:
* legalCompanyName: String - As per Commercial Register (Handelsregister).
* uidNumber: String (Format: CHE-XXX.XXX.XXX) - Crucial Swiss Enterprise ID.
* vatNumber: String (Optional, e.g., CHE-XXX.XXX.XXX MWST/TVA/IVA - Often linked to UID but sometimes listed separately).
* companyType: String Enum ('AG', 'GmbH', 'Sole Proprietorship (Einzelunternehmen)', 'Association (Verein)', 'Foundation (Stiftung)', 'Partnership (Kollektivgesellschaft/Kommanditgesellschaft)', ...) - Legal form.
* cantonOfRegistration: String (e.g., 'GE', 'ZH', 'VD') - Canton where legally registered.
* commercialRegisterNumber: String (Optional, legacy ID, e.g., CH-XXX.X.XXX.XXX-X)
* dateOfIncorporation: Timestamp / ISO String (Optional)
* legalPurpose: String (Brief description from Commercial Register, optional).
* authorizedSignatories: Array&lt;Map> ({ firstName: String, lastName: String, title: String, signatureType: String ('individual', 'collective_two', ...) }) - Key personnel from Handelsregister.

2. contactPoints (Map) - Official Addresses & Communication
* Purpose: Verifiable addresses and primary contact channels for the business. Moderate sensitivity.
* Fields:
* registeredAddress: Map ({ street: String, number: String, postalCode: String, city: String, canton: String, country: 'CH' }) - Essential legal address.
* operatingAddress: Map (Same structure, optional, if different from registered address).
* generalPhone: String (Main contact number).
* generalEmail: String (Main contact email).
* websiteUrl: String (Official company website).

3. profilePublic (Map) - Public-Facing Information & Branding
* Purpose: Information displayed to potential hires and the public on the platform. Low sensitivity.
* Fields:
* displayName: String (Brand name or common name, might differ from legal name).
* logoUrl: String (URL to logo image).
* industrySector: String (e.g., 'pharmacy', 'medical_clinic', 'hospitality', 'construction') - Reflects primarySector from users doc.
* subSectorOrSpecialization: String (Optional, e.g., 'Retail Pharmacy', 'Dental Clinic').
* companySizeRange: String Enum ('1-10 employees', '11-50', '51-200', '201-500', '501+').
* descriptionPublic: String (Company mission, values, culture, what it's like to work there).
* operatingLocations: Array&lt;Map> (If multiple sites - { name: String, address: Map, isPrimary: Boolean }).

4. operationalEnvironment (Map) - Internal Workings & Tools
* Purpose: Details about the work environment, including software used and relevant labor agreements. Moderate sensitivity.
* Fields:
* primarySoftwareUsed: Array&lt;Map> (Key systems relevant to employees)
* [{ category: String ('Pharmacy Mgmt', 'EMR/PMS', 'Accounting/Payroll', 'HRIS', 'Time Tracking', 'ERP', 'Office Suite', 'Communication'), name: String, version: String (Optional) }]
* Examples: ProPharmaX, Aeskulap, Vitomed, Bexio, Abacus, Winbiz, Sage, SAP, SuccessFactors, Clockodo, Microsoft 365, Slack.
* collectiveLaborAgreementInfo: Map ({ applies: Boolean, agreementName: String ('e.g., L-GAV Hospitality', 'LMV Construction', 'CLA Cleaning'), isDeclaredUniversal: Boolean, detailsUrl: String (Optional) }) - Very important for relevant sectors.
* standardWorkWeekHours: Number (e.g., 42, 40 - depends on sector/GAV/company policy).
* workingHoursModel: String Enum ('Fixed Schedule', 'Flextime', 'Trust-Based', 'Annualized Hours').
* remoteWorkPolicy: String Enum ('On-Site Only', 'Hybrid Flexible', 'Hybrid Structured', 'Fully Remote Possible', 'Role Dependent').
* employeeBenefitsSummary: String (Optional text describing key benefits like pension contributions above minimum, health insurance support, training budgets, transport allowances, etc.).

5. recruitmentAndContracts (Map) - Hiring Processes & Standards
* Purpose: Defines how the employer typically hires and standard contractual elements. Internal/Moderate sensitivity.
* Fields:
* hiringContactPerson: Map (Optional { name: String, email: String, phone: String, title: String }) - Specific contact for job applications.
* hiringProcessOverview: String (Optional, e.g., "Application Review -> Phone Screen -> Technical Interview -> Final Interview").
* standardProbationPeriodDays: Number (e.g., 90 - Max 3 months legally unless specified otherwise).
* standardNoticePeriodPolicy: String (e.g., "According to Swiss Code of Obligations Art. 335c", "As per GAV/CCT", "3 months after probation").
* typicalOnboardingDocumentsRequired: Array&lt;String> ('ID/Passport Copy', 'AHV Card Copy', 'Bank Details (IBAN)', 'Work Permit Copy', 'Residence Permit Copy', 'Signed Contract', 'CV', 'Diplomas/Certificates').
* contractManagement: Map ({ usesPlatformTemplates: Boolean, requiresWetSignature: Boolean, digitalSignatureMethod: String ('QES', 'AES', 'None') }).

6. payrollAndComplianceInfo (Map) - Employer Payroll Obligations & Setup
* Purpose: Information related to the employer's setup for handling mandatory Swiss payroll deductions and compliance. Internal Use / High sensitivity related to specific fund numbers.
* Fields:
* compensationFundInfo: Map ({ canton: String, fundName: String, employerAffiliationNumber: String }) - For AHV/IV/EO, FAK.
* accidentInsuranceProvider: Map ({ providerName: String, policyNumber: String }) - Mandatory UVG/LAA.
* occupationalPensionProvider: Map ({ providerName: String, contractNumber: String, contributionPlanSummary: String }) - Mandatory BVG/LPP if applicable.
* sicknessInsuranceProvider: Map (Optional KTG/IJM - { providerName: String, policyNumber: String, coveragePercentage: Number, waitingDays: Number }).
* payrollFrequency: String ('Monthly' - standard in CH).
* payslipDeliveryMethod: String ('Digital Platform', 'Email PDF', 'Paper').

7. platformAccountAndBilling (Map) - Relationship with Your Platform
* Purpose: Managing the employer's subscription, payment, and admin users on your platform. Moderate-High sensitivity.
* Fields:
* platformBillingContact: Map ({ name: String, email: String, address: Map }) - Where your invoices go.
* platformSubscriptionPlan: String (Your defined plan names).
* platformPaymentMethod: Map ({ type: String ('Credit Card', 'Direct Debit (LSV+/DD)', 'Invoice'), status: String, details: Map (Securely tokenized/masked info) }).
* billingCycle: String ('monthly', 'annually').
* nextBillingDate: Timestamp.
* accountAdminUserIds: Array&lt;String> (Link to users who manage this profile).

8. verification (Map) - Platform Verification Status
* Purpose: Tracks the verification checks performed by your platform to ensure employer legitimacy. Moderate sensitivity.
* Fields:
* overallStatus: String ('unverified', 'pending', 'verified', 'requires_attention', 'rejected').
* lastVerifiedAt: Timestamp.
* verifiedBy: String (Platform Admin/System ID).
* identityCheck: Map ({ method: String ('UID Lookup', 'Commercial Register Extract Review'), status: String, documentRefs: Array<String> }).
* sectorComplianceCheck: Map (Sector-specific checks)
* Example Pharmacy: { cantonalPermitVerified: Boolean, permitExpiry: Timestamp, documentRefs: Array<String> }
* Example Temporary Work Agency: { SECO_LicenseVerified: Boolean, licenseExpiry: Timestamp }
* verificationDocumentsProvided: Array&lt;Map> ({ documentId: String, type: String ('commercial_register_extract', 'operating_license', 'insurance_confirmation'), fileName: String, storageUrl: String, uploadedAt: Timestamp, status: String }).
* rejectionReason: String (If applicable).

