###Collection: professionalProfiles

Document ID: profileId (Unique ID, referenced in the users document)
userId: String (Back-reference to the users document) - Top Level
1. identity (Map) - Core Identification & Legal Prerequisites
* Purpose: Fundamental, legally required identification details. High sensitivity.
* Fields:
* legalFirstName: String - Required for contracts & payroll.
* legalLastName: String - Required for contracts & payroll.
* dateOfBirth: Timestamp / ISO String - Required for age verification, contracts, social security.
* nationality: String - Required for work permit status.
* ahvNumber: String (Swiss Social Security Number / AVS) - Essential for employment and social contributions. High sensitivity.

2. contact (Map) - Communication & Residence
* Purpose: How to contact the individual and their official place of residence. Moderate sensitivity.
* Fields:
* primaryPhone: String - For direct communication, notifications.
* primaryEmail: String - Contact email (may differ from login), notifications.
* residentialAddress: Map ({ street: String, number: String, postalCode: String, city: String, canton: String, country: 'CH' }) - Essential for contracts, tax calculation, legal notices.

3. employmentEligibility (Map) - Right-to-Work Status
* Purpose: Information determining the legal right to work in Switzerland. Crucial for employers before hiring. Moderate sensitivity.
* Fields:
* workPermit: Map (Required if non-Swiss/EU/EFTA) - { type: String ('L', 'B', 'C', 'G', ...), permitNumber: String, expiryDate: Timestamp, issuingCanton: String }
* crossBorderPermitDetails: Map (If workPermit.type == 'G') - { primaryEmployerName: String, primaryWorkCanton: String } (Optional, context-dependent)

4. profileDisplay (Map) - Public-Facing Profile Information
* Purpose: Information generally considered less sensitive, often used for profile visibility, searching, and matching by employers.
* Fields:
* displayName: String (Optional, e.g., "Dr. MÃ¼ller")
* profilePictureUrl: String (Optional, URL to storage)
* languagesSpoken: Array&lt;Map> (e.g., [{ language: 'German', level: 'native' }, { language: 'English', level: 'C1' }])
* bioOrSummary: String (Professional introduction)
* experienceYears: Number (Calculated or entered)
* availabilitySummary: String (e.g., "Available Part-Time (60%) from July 2025 in Canton Zurich") - Derived from platformSettings?

5. professionalDetails (Map) - Skills, Qualifications & Experience
* Purpose: Detailed professional background used for matching and verification. Moderate sensitivity.
* Fields:
* mainProfession: String (e.g., 'pharmacist' - reflects primaryProfession from users doc)
* specializations: Array&lt;String> (e.g., ['Community Pharmacy', 'Clinical Pharmacy'])
* skills: Array&lt;String> (Keywords for searching, e.g., 'vaccination', 'compounding', 'team leadership')
* softwareProficiency: Array&lt;Map> (e.g., [{ name: 'PharmaGestionX', level: 'expert' }, { name: 'MS Excel', level: 'advanced' }])
* qualifications: Array&lt;Map> (Licenses, Diplomas, Certs)
* Example: [{ type: 'federal_diploma_pharmacy', identifier: 'GLN: 7601...', dateIssued: Timestamp, issuingBody: 'BAG/OFSP', verifiedStatus: 'verified' }, { type: 'fph_vaccination_cert', validUntil: Timestamp, verifiedStatus: 'pending' }]
* workExperience: Array&lt;Map> (Optional, simplified employment history - { jobTitle: String, companyName: String, period: String, description: String })

6. payrollData (Map) - Salary Calculation & Payslip Generation
* Purpose: Information strictly necessary for calculating salary, deductions, taxes, and generating legal payslips. Highest Sensitivity - Strong Access Control Needed.
* Fields:
* civilStatus: String Enum ('single', 'married', 'registered_partnership', 'divorced', 'widowed') - Affects tax, some benefits.
* numberOfChildren: Number - Required for Family Allowances (Kinderzulagen).
* childrenDetails: Array&lt;Map> (Optional, only if DOB needed for specific allowance rules/age brackets { dob: Timestamp }) - Minimize collection.
* withholdingTaxInfo: Map ({ isSubject: Boolean, taxCanton: String, rateGroup: String ('A0N', 'B1Y', 'C2N', ...) }) - Required for those subject to Quellensteuer.
* religion: String Enum ('Roman Catholic', 'Protestant', 'Christian Catholic', 'Other/None') - For church tax in applicable cantons. Should ideally be optional/user-controlled.
* workPercentageDefault: Number (Optional default Pensum, e.g., 100)

7. banking (Map) - Salary Payment
* Purpose: Bank account details for receiving salary payments. Highest Sensitivity - Strong Access Control Needed.
* Fields:
* iban: String (Primary field for payments within CH/EU)
* bankName: String (Helpful for identification/validation)
* accountHolderName: String (Must match legal name, usually)
* bicSwift: String (Optional, fallback/international context)
* bankClearingNumber: String (BCN - Optional, sometimes still used in CH alongside IBAN)

8. platformSettings (Map) - User Preferences for Platform Usage
* Purpose: How the user wants to interact with the platform. Low sensitivity.
* Fields:
* detailedAvailability: Map ({ availabilityType: String ('full-time', 'part-time', 'temporary'), minHoursPerWeek: Number, maxHoursPerWeek: Number, preferredWorkdays: Array<String>, preferredCantons: Array<String>, noticePeriodDays: Number, earliestStartDate: Timestamp, notes: String })

9. verification (Map) - Status of Verified Information
* Purpose: Tracks the verification status of different aspects of the profile. Moderate sensitivity.
* Fields:
* identityStatus: String ('unverified', 'pending', 'verified', 'rejected')
* qualificationsStatus: String ('unverified', 'pending', 'verified', 'rejected')
* workEligibilityStatus: String ('unverified', 'pending', 'verified', 'rejected')
* overallVerificationStatus: String ('unverified', 'pending', 'verified', 'rejected')
* lastVerifiedAt: Timestamp
* verifiedBy: String (Admin/System ID)
* verificationDocuments: Array&lt;Map> ({ documentId: String, type: String ('id_card', 'diploma', 'permit', 'cv'), fileName: String, storageUrl: String, uploadedAt: Timestamp, status: String ('pending_review', 'approved', 'rejected'), rejectionReason: String })

